---- Register ----

16 Register insgesamt => 4 bit
Carry-Register, PC

Op-Code Breite: 7 bit


Assembler-Befehle

---- ALU (16 Befehle => 4 bit) ----

-- Arithmetische Operationen --

add: dest, src1, src2
addi: dest, src1, imm
addc: dest, src1, src2
addci: dest, src1, imm

sub: dest, src1, src2
subi: dest, src1, imm
subc: dest, src1, src2
subci: dest, src1, imm

-mul: dest, src1, src2
-muli: dest, src, imm
-mulc: dest, src1, src2
-mulci: dest, src, imm

-div: dest, src1, src2
-divi: dest, src, imm
-divc: dest, src1, src2
-divci: dest, src, imm


-- Logische Operationen --

slli: dest, imm
slri: dest, imm

-sali: dest, imm
-sari: dest, imm

sb: dest, imm
ub: dest, imm // not necessary

rr: dest, imm
rl: dest, imm

cmpe: src1, src2
cmpg: src1, src2
-cmpl: src1, src2

xor: dest, src1, src2
or: dest, src1, src2
and: dest, src1, src2
xnor: dest, src1, src2
nor: dest, src1, src2


---- Speicher ----

loadI: imm, src
storeI: imm, src

mov: dest, src

movui: dest, imm
movli: dest, imm


---- Flusskontrolle ----

# PC zu einer absoluten Speicheradresse springen
jmp: imm

# Relativ
bt: imm
bf: imm


|| Requires further specification

Little or Big Endian (probably little endian?)
How large is the memory?
\- Where to store the stack?

Some instructions are not necessarily needed
and could be freed up to allow other more
necessary instructions:

- remove "xor", "xnor", "nor" and add "not" to "or", "and"
  ("xor", "xnor", "nor" can be added if there are some
  opcodes left - these will definitely be pseudo-opcodes)
- sb and ub are pseudo-opcodes and are to be merged for
  hardware (7bit + 1bit (set or unset) + 4bit + 6bit)
- remove arithmetic immediate instructions that use the
  carry; there are only edge-cases where they would be
  useful
- add arithmetic shifts to the ALU
- "call", "push" and "pop" as pseudo-opcode
- assembler instructions notated with . (.data $var "data")
- registers should start with "%" and either numeric or some
  names
- return address register (or just repurposed general purpose register?)

- use 'escaped' for comments
